<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-04T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="636" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.90G2/32: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Barbour</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-04T20:00:00-04:00">August 4, 1938—8
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>15. Your 18, July 28, noon. Alternative (2) acceptable. How soon can
                                treaty be prepared for signature? Department would like to <pb facs="0777" n="769" xml:id="pg_769"/> have it signed at earliest
                                date practicable. Will Iraq Government accept telegraphic full
                                powers?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>